---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/seo/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { CONTACT_EMAIL } from '../config';

// NOTE (internal, not rendered): this is a standard, conservative starting
// policy. Confirm the legal entity name, governing jurisdiction, data-processor
// list, and retention periods with counsel before relying on it.
const lastUpdated = 'July 2026';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | GovHub"
  description="How GovHub collects, uses, and protects your data across its AI government proposal and compliance platform."
>
  <main class="container">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[{ name: 'Home', url: '/' }, { name: 'Privacy', url: '/privacy/' }]} />

    <article class="prose">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <div class="gh-divider-ridge" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how GovHub ("GovHub," "we," "us") collects,
        uses, and protects information when you use our website and platform (the
        "Services"). By using the Services, you agree to the practices described
        here.
      </p>

      <h2>1. Information we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Account information</strong> you provide, such as name, work email, company, and role.</li>
        <li><strong>Content you upload,</strong> including solicitations, past-performance data, and proposal drafts.</li>
        <li><strong>Usage data,</strong> such as log and device information collected automatically when you use the Services.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>2. How we use information</h2>
      <p>
        We use information to provide, operate, secure, and improve the Services;
        to draft and review your proposals at your direction; to communicate with
        you; and to comply with legal obligations. We do not use your uploaded
        proposal content to train AI models.
      </p>

      <h2>3. How we share information</h2>
      <p>
        We share information with service providers who process data on our behalf
        under appropriate confidentiality and security obligations, and where
        required by law. We do not sell your personal information.
      </p>

      <h2>4. Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We retain information for as long as your account is active or as needed to
        provide the Services, and thereafter as required for legitimate business or
        legal purposes. You may request deletion as described below.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We protect information using encryption in transit and at rest, access
        controls, and tenant isolation. See the <a href="/security/">security
        page</a> for details.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, export,
        or delete your personal information. To exercise these rights, contact us at
        <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        We use cookies and similar technologies to operate the site and understand
        usage. You can control cookies through your browser settings.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Children's privacy</h2>
      <p>The Services are not directed to children and we do not knowingly collect data from them.</p>

      <h2>9. Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. Material changes will be
        reflected by the "Last updated" date above.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy? Email
        <a href={`mailto:${CONTACT_EMAIL}`}>{CONTACT_EMAIL}</a>.
      </p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  main { padding: 1rem 1.5rem 3rem; }
  .prose { max-width: 44rem; margin: 1rem 0; }
  .updated { color: var(--fg-muted); font-size: 0.9rem; }
  h2 { margin-top: 2rem; font-size: 1.25rem; }
  ul { padding-left: 1.25rem; color: var(--fg-muted); }
  li { margin: 0.4rem 0; }
  p { color: var(--fg-muted); }
</style>
